Field Descriptions: Value of “1” given to a generic prescription, “0” given to a brand. Using
the Gen Ind-Medispan values as listed:
Example: A generic claim for Fluoxetine would have a claim counter
value 1.  Following is the specific log
Count of net prescriptions that are on the formulary. Set to either 1 for
paid, captured or -1 for paid reversed, captured reverse when
Formulary Flag field is set to "Y"
The submitted Rx number on the transaction.
Identifies the type of data being submitted in the ‘Rx Number’ field.
Code indicating the quantity dispensed is a partial fill or the completion
of a partial fill. Used only in situations where inventory shortages do
not allow the full quantity to be dispensed.
Submitted date the prescription was filled. (format: YYYYMMDD)
Identifies the type of data being submitted in the Product ID field.
